<1ST_LINE>u a AM-PrisonEscapees     03-28 0317</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Prison Escapees,0325</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Officers Capture Armed Escapees In Stolen Car</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SHELTON, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three prison escapees including a triple
murderer were captured Sunday night in a stolen car after four days
of freedom in which they found a gun and allegedly committed a
robbery, authorities say.
   No one was injured when the car in which the three were riding
was surrounded by law enforcement officers outside this town, said
Mason County sheriff's Lt. Howard Armsfield. He said a handgun was
stuffed under the seat of the car.
   The three escaped Wednesday night from the Washington
Corrections Center in Shelton, about 15 miles northwest of Olympia
in western Washington, authorities said.
   They apparently had been hiding in a shed near a home about
three miles from the prison, Armsfield said.
   Armed with a gun they found in the shed, the three confronted
the people who lived in the house on Sunday afternoon, robbed them
of a few dollars and stole their auto, he said.
   Armsfield said he did not have additional details of the
robbery. Mason County Sheriff Bob Holter said earlier he believed
the residents were unharmed.
   The convicts first drove off in a pickup truck, and abandoned it
and another stolen car before seizing the car in which they were
captured, Armsfield said.
   One of the escapees, Sean Stevenson, 17, was convicted of
murdering his mother, stepfather and sister. He went to prison June
20 on a sentence of life without possibility of parole.
   With him were Gary Curtis Van Winkle, 17, convicted of attempted
murder and burglary, and Patrick J. Rice, 23, convicted of 10
counts of second-degree burglary and one count of taking a motor
vehicle without permission.
   The three escaped after apparently scaling a chain link fence
topped with three feet of razor-sharp ``ribbon wire'' at a point
close to an unoccupied prison guard tower, said Corrections
Department spokeswoman Barbara Lovelace.
</TEXT>
