<2ND_LINE>AM-Japan-Markets, 2nd Ld-Writethru, a0848,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Dollar Falls, Stock Prices Rise</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 3 grafs to UPDATE with closing dollar, stock
prices. Pickup 4th graf pvs ``Traders said...''</NOTE>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The dollar fell sharply against the Japanese yen in
Tokyo Monday while stock prices rose.
   The dollar closed at 124.43 yen, down 1.31 yen from Friday's
close of 125.74 yen, after opening the day's session at 124.60.
   On the Tokyo Stock Exchange, the Nikkei Stock Average of 225
selected issues, which lost 305.99 points in Saturday's half day of
trading, rose 301.99 points, or 1.19 percent, and closed at
25,622.71.
   Traders said the dollar continued to decline even after the Bank
of Japan intervened in early trading by buying dollars to support
the U.S. currency, said Ken Iio, a currency dealer with the Bank of
Tokyo.
   The dollar's opening level was its lowest since Jan. 5, when it
began trading at 123.00 yen.
   On the stock market, dealers said the lower dollar did not
affect prices because market participants were expecting the
central bank to continue to prop up the U.S. currency.
</TEXT>
