<2ND_LINE>PM-British Stocks,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Share Prices Move Lower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices dropped on the London Stock Exchange
today morning as investors reacted to Friday's plunge on Wall
Street.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index fell 16.8
points, or 1 percent, to 1,751.1 by 11 a.m.
   Shares prices fell despite a recovery in Tokyo share prices
earlier today.
   However, dealers said the London market didn't have much
direction of its own, with little trading taking place ahead of the
extended Easter holiday weekend that will begin Friday.
   Major shares were down across the board, with some composite
insurance stocks showing the only rise.
   The early trend followed the sharp fall in New York Friday,
where the Dow Jones Industrial Average fell 44.92 to 1,978.95, and
gains in Tokyo overnight, where the Nikkei index rose 301.99 to
25,622.71.
</TEXT>
