<HEAD>New Postal Card Features Bison</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bison roam a grassy prairie on a new postal
card being issued today in Buffalo, Wyoming, the U.S. Postal
Service reports.
   The card will be the first to carry the new 15-cent postage rate
for cards, which takes effect Sunday.
   It is the first in a new ``America the Beautiful'' series of
postal cards being issued by the Postal Service. The design of
bison with mountains in the background was adapted from a painting
by Bart Forbes of Dallas.
