<HEAD>Two Women Wounded In Church Shooting</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man demanding the return of his
adopted daughter fired into a group of people getting out of a
church school van, hitting the girl's biological mother and
seriously wounding her cousin.
   The Fort Worth Police Department issued a warrant for the arrest
of Ollie Thomas, 74, on two counts of attempted murder, spokesman
Tom Wayne said Sunday. Police said he remained at large today.
   Bridgett Shirley, 14, was in serious condition today in an
intensive care unit after undergoing 3{ hours of surgery for a
gunshot wound to the lower back, hospital spokesmen said.
   The shooting took place at 9 a.m. Sunday outside Samaritan
Church of God in Christ, police said.
   Van passengers told police a man with a gun stopped the van
during its pick-up route and told them he was looking for his
16-year-old adopted daughter, Carmel Shirley, who had left home a
few weeks ago.
   When the van arrived at the church, the same gunman was waiting.
   ``He was just hollering `I want my baby,''' said Earnestine
Shirley, 33, who is Carmel's mother and Bridgett's aunt. ``He was
talking about killing up the whole family.''
   The crowd of about 15 to 20 scattered as the man started
shooting, witnesses said.
   One bullet pierced Earnestine Shirley's elbow and another struck
Bridgett. The gunman fired several times at Laura Shirley,
Bridgett's mother, but never wounded her.
   Carmel Shirley had planned to arrive at the church later and
wasn't with the other members of her family.
   Earnestine Shirley was treated for the elbow wound and released
from hospital. Laura Shirley was treated for knee scrapes and
released.
   According to the Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Earnestine Shirley
said she became pregnant at 14 and six years later asked an older
couple to temporarily take care of her child. Later she learned the
couple adopted the girl, she said.
   But three weeks ago, she said Carmel, now 16, returned to her
alleging that Thomas, her adoptive father, had mistreated her since
she was 8.
