<HEAD>Boy Dies After Falling From The Orbiter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAUDERDALE LAKES, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 15-year-old boy fell 20 feet to
his death after he climbed up from under the safety bar on a
carnival ride called The Orbiter, an official said.
   Demetrick Welch of Lauderhill fell when he either tried to get
out of his seat or change seats with his sister, Broward County
sheriff's spokesman Al Gordon said Sunday.
   The ride, owned by Crown Amusements of Apollo Beach, is designed
to keep passengers in their seats with centrifugal force. It has
several arms, each holding three two-seat buckets. Each bucket has
a safety bar that locks across riders.
   Crown Amusements ride superintendent Don Bodami told deputies
that no riders had been injured since The Orbiter was purchased new
in 1985. Each ride is checked daily, and The Orbiter passed a state
safety inspection last week, he said.
</TEXT>
