<HEAD>Trumpeter Released From Hospital</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Trumpeter Al Hirt was released from the hospital
Monday after a four-day stay for treatment of a hand and arm
ailment, officials said.
   ``He had been treated by Dr. Michael DeBakey for an acute
infection of the right hand and arm, which is his playing hand,''
said Methodist Hospital spokeswoman Brenda Blake. ``The outlook is
excellent.''
   Hirt, 65, flew to Houston on Thursday from his home in New
Orleans so he could be treated by DeBakey, a friend.
   Hirt said his doctors believed the problem may be related to his
trumpet playing and a growth that developed on a finger of his
right hand after 59 years of playing.
   Hirt canceled an appearance Thursday in New Orleans and a
weekend gig in Fairfield, Conn., so he could be treated.
