<HEAD>Thatcher Says Reagan Looks Strong</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher said Monday she
sees no signs that President Reagan is becoming a lame duck.
   The British leader told the British Broadcasting Corp. in a
radio interview that the president is ``cantering up to a very
strong finish.''
   ``I mean, there's no sign of slowing down at all. If anything,
it's a very, very strong finish,'' she said.
   Asked whether she will consider herself leader of the Western
world while a new U.S. president settles in, Mrs. Thatcher said
there ``can be no substitute for American leadership _ there just
can't.''
   ``They're strong, they're enterprising, they somehow keep that
country going through difficulties with elections,'' she said.
