<HEAD>Stock Prices Move Lower on Wall Street</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: grafs 1-3 new to UPDATE with 11 a.m. Dow and CORRECT to
declines outnumbering advances. Picks up 4th graf pvs: Analysts had
...</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices steadied at lower levels in edgy
trading today as bearish sentiment spilled over from last week, the
worst trading week so far this year.
   On Wall Street, the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off
9.45 points at 1,969.50 at 11 a.m. EST. The key index fell 44.92
points on Friday and 43.77 points on Thursday.
   Ten stock issues declined in price for every three that rose on
the New York Stock Exchange in the early going.
   Analysts had expected further downward movement following the
losses late last week.
   Stocks succumbed to additional pressure from a softer dollar,
which continued to fall against major foreign currencies in Europe
after closing at its lowest level in three months in Tokyo.
   Despite the bearish sentiment in the equities market, traders
did not expect another ``Black Monday'' in today's session, said
Larry Wachtel, an analyst at Prudential-Bache Securities Inc.
   The Dow's historic 508-point plunge on Oct. 19 followed sharp
losses on the previous Friday. But Wachtel said market participants
anticipated the market would settle down after initial losses today.
