<HEAD>Control Data To Buy 20 Percent Of Silicon Graphics</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Control Data Corp. will buy a 20 percent stake
in Silicon Graphics Inc. for $68.9 million in a step intended to
cement their business relationship, the computer companies said
Monday.
   Minneapolis-based Control Data said it intended to buy $150
million worth of computer workstations from Silicon Graphics over
the next three years, continuing an arrangement with the Mountain
View, Calif.-based company that dates back to late 1986. The
companies will cooperate on developing new workstations.
   Control Data will buy newly issued shares of common stock in
Silicon Graphics at a price of $22.50 a share that will represent
20 percent of the company's stock.
