<2ND_LINE>AM-Auto Incentives,0144</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Chevy Extends Car, Truck Rebates</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp.'s Chevrolet division is
extending rebates ranging from $400 to $1,200 on several cars and
trucks, the company said Monday.
   The incentives, which were to expire April 30, will run through
May 11.
   They include rebates of $1,200 to import owners buying the
subcompact Chevrolet Nova, built at a Toyota-run joint-venture
factory in Fremont, Calif. Non-import owners receive a $600 rebate
on Nova.
   Other rebates include: $400 on Chevrolet Cavalier, $500 on
Beretta, Spectrum, S-10 pickup and Blazer, full-size pickup and
cab-and-chassis and Chevy Van and Sportvan; $750 on Camaro and
Celebrity and $1,000 on Spectrum Turbo and Camaro in Hawaii and
California.
   The rebate can be taken as cash or used for a down payment.
Buyers must take delivery by the campaign's expiration.
