<1ST_LINE>r f AM-AlliedSignal     03-28 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Allied Signal,0135</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Company Announces Election of New President and CEO</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MORRIS TOWNSHIP, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An executive vice president of
Allied Signal Inc. has been chosen the company's president and
chief operating officer, officials of the advanced techonolgy firm
announced Monday.
   Alan Belzer, who has also been president of the company's $2.8
billion engineered materials sector, will assume his new posts
April 1, said Edward L. Hennessy, chairman and chief executive
officer of Allied Signal.
   Hennessy said the materials sector under Belzer, 55, has been
the most consistently profitable of Allied Signal's three operating
units.
   ``In his new position, Alan will oversee the day-to-day
operations of the company's successful core businesses in
aerospace, engineered materials and automotive products,'' Hennessy
said.
   Belzer, 55, joined Allied Signal in 1955.
</TEXT>
